						<summary>A list of 4 <foreign>biruda</foreign>s on a capital stone found lying around the Shore temple.</summary>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc>
						<handDesc>
							<p>There are two scripts used. The honorific <foreign>śrī</foreign> is written in Siddhamātṛkā, while the rest of the inscription is in Grantha. The double <foreign>daṇḍa</foreign> is of the type where both <foreign>daṇḍa</foreign>s are joined.</p>
							<p>A rapprocher des biruda des chapelles du Kailāsanātha.</p>
